# 🎣 Phishing Detector

Professional phishing URL detection with ML, VirusTotal API, HTML reports, and a Flask web dashboard.

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

### 1. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2. (Optional) Add VirusTotal API key
- Get a FREE key at: https://www.virustotal.com/gui/join-us
- Open `config.py` and replace `YOUR_VT_API_KEY` with your key

### 3. Run the dashboard
```bash
python app.py
```

### 4. Open in browser
```
http://localhost:5000
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
phishing_pro/
├── app.py                  # Flask web dashboard
├── detector.py             # Core ML + rules + VirusTotal engine
├── report_generator.py     # HTML report exporter
├── config.py               # API keys & settings
├── requirements.txt
├── phishing_history.db     # SQLite scan history (auto-created)
└── reports/                # Downloaded HTML reports (auto-created)
```

---

## 🧠 How It Works

### Detection Engine (2 layers)
| Layer | Weight | Description |
|---|---|---|
| Rule Engine | 40% | 20+ heuristic checks |
| ML Model | 60% | Random Forest classifier |

### Risk Score
| Score | Verdict |
|---|---|
| 70–100 | 🔴 PHISHING |
| 40–69 | 🟡 SUSPICIOUS |
| 0–39 | 🟢 LIKELY SAFE |

### Features checked
- IP address in URL
- Suspicious TLDs (.tk .ml .xyz .cf etc)
- Brand spoofing in subdomain
- URL length & entropy
- @ symbol, double slashes
- Encoded characters
- URL shorteners
- HTTPS presence
- Keyword analysis (login, verify, secure...)

---

## 🌐 VirusTotal Integration
Enable the checkbox in the dashboard to check URLs against 70+ antivirus engines via the VirusTotal API.
Free API key allows 500 lookups/day.

---

## 📊 HTML Reports
Click **Download HTML Report** after any scan to get a standalone HTML file with:
- Verdict & risk score
- All triggered risk factors
- VirusTotal results
- Full extracted features table

---

## ⚠️ Legal Notice
For educational and research use only. Only scan URLs you have permission to test.
